<p>
 My Japanese is (very) slowly progressing. I'm ditching my current
 study book "Japanese for busy people" because I got bored 
 of Mr. Smith's (that is, <em>Su-mi-su-san</em>) and Mr. Brown's (<em>Bu-ra-u-n-san</em>)
 business trips and meetings. The most exciting story
 was chapter 7 when they take a break and go to a Sumo match.
 I was excited to read about some real action, but then I
 peeked at the end of the book just to find a uninteresting story
 in which they walk together to the public library. Will Mr.Smith be able
 to get a membership card? This suspense is not solved in
 the last chapter, when Mr. Smith writes a boring letter to his sensei.
 
 </p>
 
